<ul class="task-constraints">
<li><b>Time limit:</b> 1.00 s</li>
<li><b>Memory limit:</b> 512 MB</li>
</ul>
<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="2195">
Given a set of $n$ points in the two-dimensional plane, your task is to determine the convex hull of the points.<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The first input line has an integer $n$: the number of points.<br />
<br />
After this, there are $n$ lines that describe the points. Each line has two integers $x$ and $y$: the coordinates of a point.<br />
<br />
You may assume that each point is distinct, and the area of the hull is positive.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
First print an integer $k$: the number of points in the convex hull.<br />
<br />
After this, print $k$ lines that describe the points. You can print the points in any order. Print all points that lie on the convex hull.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$3 \le n \le 2 \cdot 10^5$<br />
<li>$-10^9 \le x, y \le 10^9$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>6<br />
2 1<br />
2 5<br />
3 3<br />
4 3<br />
4 4<br />
6 3</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>4<br />
2 1<br />
2 5<br />
4 4<br />
6 3</code>    </div>
